  <h2>Our Mission</h2>
  <p>At our hospital, we strive to make excellent medical diagnostic services accessible to Nigerians.</p>

  <p>Our presence in Nigeria will increase our capacity to provide proper service delivery to our patients and doctors.</p>

  

  <p>To help us achieve this, we must:</p>
  <br />

  <strong>Be The Leader In Medical Diagnostics</strong>

  <p>Our goal is to position our hospital as the clear leader in medical diagnostics in Nigeria, West Africa and Africa. We strive to have the most dedicated employees in the industry, and we are committed to skills development and training and ensuring a positive work culture and room for growth at all times.</p>

  

  <strong>Drive Digitised Processes</strong>

  <p>To stay at the forefront of the sector, we strive to be a digital company focused on driving efficiencies through technology and innovation, delivering faster outcomes, improving patient care, streamlining processes and creating value-added workflows.</p>

  

  <strong>Foster And Promote Sustainability</strong>

  <p>We strive to be a pioneer in the Nigerian healthcare sector using sustainable energy in line with WHO goal for hospitals to become carbon neutral all over the world.</p>

  

  <strong>Expand Public-Private-Partnerships</strong>

  <p>One of the challenges we face in Nigeria is access to quality health services. The government has many responsibilities in different sectors but have limited resources. For this reason, we support government institutions through public-private partnerships to provide quality and accessible healthcare to our people. We currently support Lagos State Teaching Hospital (LUTH), Maternal and Child Care (MCC) Hospital Ajah, and Delta State University Teaching Hospital (DELSUTH) in this regard. Our goal is to make excellent medical diagnostics accessible in sub-Saharan Africa, starting with Nigeria.</p>

  <p>Due to the challenges of managing health facilities in Nigeria and the significant investment required to establish and operate a standard facility, there is an urgent need for the government to work with the private sector to accelerate access to quality healthcare in the country.</p>

  <p>To achieve this, a public-private partnership framework is envisioned.</p>

  <p>Through our PPP framework, the government will have access to the capital and skills (management and technical) it needs to drive advancements in the sector it wants to improve.</p>

  <p>Our partnerships are structured to ensure a win-win scenario to collaborate with the government to deliver effective solutions to manage infrastructure deficiencies in all sectors and address the challenges of providing quality health services.</p>
  <br />
  

  <h2>Commitment to Quality and Reliability</h2>
  <p>WE are the first medical laboratory in West Africa to achieve ISO 15189 international accreditation in 2006, setting the benchmark for quality analysis in Nigeria.</p>

  <p>We are unique in Africa because of the special attention and care given to patients from outstanding service delivery, improved operational efficiency, innovation and investment in state-of-the-art diagnostic technology. We are committed to best practices and the highest ethical standards.</p>
  

  <strong>Organisational Goals</strong>
  <ul>
    <li>To domesticate tests that are currently referred to reference laboratories abroad by building local capacity and training staff with the necessary skills. This will lead to better service delivery and reduced turnaround times.</li>
    <li>To expand our national footprint and make reliable testing accessible across a broader geographic region. </li>
    <li>To achieve 80% turnaround time at all locations and effectively resolve customer complaints.</li>
    <li>To achieve all external quality controls in all disciplines (Haematology, Serology, Endocrinology, Chemistry, Microbiology, and Histopathology) to a standard recognised by international authorities.</li>
